The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Relief forecast

 Calcutta, July 7: The weather in Calcutta and the rest of south Bengal will improve in the next 24 hours as the depression has moved away, Met officials said today.

 However, the sky over Calcutta and its adjoining districts is likely to remain cloudy and there might be a few spells of rain and thundershower. The weatherman warned of heavy rain in isolated places in the other south Bengal districts.

 The deep depression that lay close to Jamshedpur last night has weakened into a depression today and is moving towards Madhya Pradesh, said G.C. Debnath, the director of the weather section at the Regional Meteorological Centre, Alipore.




